Continuing from the other PR:

@vihdzp said:
> You don't usually see explicit equivalences when doing cardinal arithmetic after a certain point, instead you just use results like Cantor-Schröder to do all the heavy lifting. So being able to abstract that away is a good thing in my book.

@b-mehta said:
> I think so too - the fact that cardinals are defined as equivalence classes of equivs should be thought of as an implementation detail, and so the congr lemmas which allow this should stay.

My weak objection here is that if the link to `Equiv` is considered an implementation detail, then we end up needing a `congr` lemma for every functorial Equiv in mathlib, which doesn't scale particularly well.

